==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: maidenhair fern
<hw>maidenhair fern</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any of various small
to large terrestrial ferns of the genus <gen>Adiantum</gen> having very
slender graceful stalks and delicate palmately branched fronds,
especially (<spn>Adiantum pedatum</spn>). It is common in the United
States, and is sometimes used in medicine. The name is also applied to
other species of the same genus, as to the Venus-hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>maidenhair berry</ent>⟦br⟧

